g.text: This example workflow implements a basic customer segmentation through a clustering procedure on a preconfigured data set. No
- Create a copy of the wf and rename it as follows: "01. Remote Workflow Execution_YourInitials"
- Upload the Workflow to KNIME Server, to the directory: Solutions -> Uploaded Workflows
- Schedule a workflow execution in 5 minutes and send yourself a notification on completion.
- Make some changes to the workflow (for instance create 5 clusters instead of 4) "01. Remote Workflow Execution_YourInitials" and re-deploy it to KNIME Server. Create
a snapshot of the workflow and check the created snapshot with the Server History view
- Download the created snapshot in the LOCAL Workspace
- Use the WorkDiff feature to compare the downloaded workflow with the latest workflow uploaded on the KNIME Server
